                    <ab>(C.) In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi dei aeterni.<persName
                            ref="#people/110" key="#Emperor/king"> Hludouuicus</persName> gratia dei
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus invictissimi domni
                        imperatoris <persName ref="#people/9" key="#Emperor/king"
                            >Hlotharii</persName> filius. Dignum est, ut, qui prudenter dei obsequia
                        ordinare procurant et hoc ad stabilitatem perpetuam nostram corroborationem
                        confirmare exposcunt, ut tanto libentius obaudivimus, quanto et deo placita
                        intelligimus et prudentia deo protegente bono studio ad effectum perducere
                        procuravimus. Igitur omnium fidelium sanctae dei aecclesiae ac nostrorum
                        praesentium scilicet et futurorum comperiat sollertia, quia, dum nos dilecto
                            <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideli</rs> nostro <persName ref="#people/1514"
                            key="#fidelisOf #rectorOf">Adalberto</persName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobium</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/301" key="#Manentes #Monasteries">domini
                            Saluatoris</orgName> in <placeName ref="#places/737"
                            key="#Manentes #Monasteries">monte Amiate</placeName> constitutum ad <rs
                            key="#rectorOf">regendum</rs> conmisissemus et ibidem neglecta dei
                        obsequia et procuratione deo ibidem famulantium praedecessorum suorum
                        incuriam multis modis repperisset, studiosius decertavit congregationem
                        monachorum ibidem deo servientium regulariter corrigere et solummodo divinis
                        obsequiis deditos ad sufficientiam suorum largire, quatenus praelatus iam
                        fati monasterii domini Saluatoris, qui per tempora fuerit, ac successorum
                        illius abbati vel praepositi cum subiectis monachis suorum inibi deo
                        servientium deinceps in futurum sufficienter habere mereantur, ob amore dei
                        remediumque animarum nostrarum [a]c successorum nostrorum regum aut
                        imperatorum conferens eis ad sufficientiam suorum <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1512"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ><rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                            <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1949">sancti Benedicti</placeName></orgName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/334"><rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> de <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/764">Palea</placeName></geogName>, cellam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/303">sancti Stephani in <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/757">Monticlo</placeName></orgName> et cellam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/302">sanctae Mariae in <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/756">Lamulas</placeName></orgName>, curticellam de
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/331"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/760">Mustia</placeName></geogName> nec non et
                        curticellam de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/335"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/1951">Titinano</placeName></geogName> et in <placeName
                            ref="#places/1952"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Dowry #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants"
                            >Cerri</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">angariales</rs> seu et in <placeName
                            ref="#places/761"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Manentes"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/2315"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Manentes"
                                >Feroniano</geogName></placeName> et <rs key="#Manentes"
                            >manentes</rs> eius nec non et cellam <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/308"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Saluatoris de <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/762">Uallerachana</placeName></orgName> et curticella
                        de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/332">Cuniclo</geogName> cum ipso Cagiolo de <placeName
                            ref="#places/1953">Portiano</placeName> et cellam <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1455"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1948">sancti Stephani</placeName></orgName> in
                            <placeName ref="#places/430">Terquini</placeName> seu et cellam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1513"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1950">sancti Seueri</placeName></orgName> super lacu
                        cum ipsa curticella de<geogName ref="#estates/333"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/1956">Bisentio</placeName></geogName>, cellam etiam
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1514"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/1955">sancti Miniati</placeName></orgName> nec non et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1515">cellulam sanctae Mariae de <placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                ref="#places/2734">Ualeriano</placeName></orgName> cum ipsas res de
                            <geogName ref="#estates/2346">Curticiole</geogName>, cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis et adiacentiis earum, ea videlicet ratione, ut ab hanc in
                        futurum praedicta sancta congregatio his omnibus denominatis cellulis et
                        curtibus cum suis omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis tantummodo suis
                        utilitatibus habentes victum vestitumque regulariter sumentes absque ulla
                        dilatione solummodo divinis die noctuque persistant obsequiis ac pro
                        stabilitate totius imperii nobis a deo commissi studeant exorare. Sed, quod
                        bono studio bonaque voluntate fecit, perennem habeat stabilitatem, petiit
                        pietatem nostram, ut eandem ordinationem nostram confirmaremus
                        conscriptionem, sicuti et fecimus. Denique etiam concedimus praedicto
                        monasterio omnia <rs key="#Decima">decima</rs>
                        <rs key="#Public_exactions #Profits_of_justice">frea et iudiciaria</rs> vel
                        omnem compositionem et exibitionem publicam ex omnibus manentibus de supra
                        memoratis cellulis et curtibus ob remedium animae nostrae successorumque
                        nostrorum regum vel imperatorum, qui per tempora fuerint, ad portam ipsius
                        monasterii conferendam semper ad usus peregrinorum sustentandos in elimoniam
                        et augmentum animarum nostrarum propter oppressiones malorum ac pravorum
                        hominum, quae sufferre minime nec sustentare potuerant. Quapropter eidem
                        sancto loco hoc nostrum praeceptum fieri iussimus, per quod praecipimus, ut
                        ab hinc in futurum eadem sanctae congregationi omni quietudine absque ullo
                        publico repetitu aut rectoris loci ipsius subtractu easdem cellulas et
                        curtes in suis utilitatibus ac necessitatibus habeant et ordinent, faciant
                        et disponant, quatenus exinde sufficientiam habentes in divinis obsequiis et
                        nobis eorum famulatio proficiat sempiternale remedium. Si quis vero, quod
                        futurum minime credimus esse, quilibet homo magna parvaque persona contra
                        hoc nostrum imperiale muniminis praeceptum temerario ausu contendere aut
                        inrumpere, molestare aut inquietare seu evacuare vel diminorare aut etiam
                        inbeneficiare predictas cellulas et curtes praesumpserit aut aliqua
                        violentia quandoque tempore inferre praesumptor extiterit, sciat se
                        compositurus <rs key="#Penalty">argenti lib. XXX et auri ebrizi lib. V</rs>,
                        medietatem <rs key="#Palatium">palatio</rs> nostro et medietatem eisdem
                        aecclesiae rectoribus. Et ut haec nostrae auctoritatis praeceptum futuris
                        temporibus domino opitulante valeat inconvulsum manere, manu propria subter
                        firmavimus et anuli nostri inpressione subter insigniri iussimus. Signum
                        (M.) domni Hludouuici serenissimi imperatoris augusti. (C.) <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Heinricus">Hericus</name></persName> domni
                        imperatoris <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            ref="#people/3906" key="#Archchancellor">Dructemiri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et (SR.)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
